Until now, I have benefited from contacts that I have obtained through the competitions.
The franchise sale of his hotel helped Lukas Pytloun to win the competition of the best individual entrepreneur.
The winner of last year's Best Individual Entrepreneur competition was 28-year-old entrepreneur Lukas Pytloun.
His adventure towards success is like in a film.
Lukas Pytloun liked to travel.
And abroad, he realized that in Libérec there was missing a quality accommodation site at a reasonable price.
From his savings on what he had earned while working abroad and with the help of a bank loan he bought a small building of 5 apartments half demolished.
Knowing that he was still a graduate student, it was a courageous action.
"The relationship between the quality and the price of accommodation in our region has made me want to do something," says Lucas Pytloun.
He began to rent the first apartment rebuilt to foreign workers.
He reinvested the profit in the building which he converted into a pension with 54 beds.
Since then, his entrepreneurial activity has enabled him to open in Libérec 4 pensions, two restaurants of style and two hotels with a total capacity of nearly 300 beds of all categories of accommodation.
The most comfortable of them was until recently the four-star Pytloun design hotel.
This year he received another one of the same quality.
"We just signed a contract with a hotel in Ostrova U Tise where we sold our franchise concept and other Pytloun franchise candidates came forward," the number 1 of last year's entrepreneurs.
"And for the sale of the license for the operation of a large-scale hotel the victory in the entrepreneur of the year contest has served well," adds Pytloun with gratitude.
Victory brought him more popularity and to be known at Liberek and its surroundings.
"People recognized me on the streets, often congratulated me and, I must say, it was very pleasant," he recalls.
It recommends participation in this competition to all those who are trying to do something.
It's not necessary to win, but any opportunity to be visible is good.
He says he's been using his contacts and knowledge until now that he couldn't have gotten in any other way.
"With those I met through the contest I started to maintain business relations regularly.
According to him, the reputation for success also had an impact on employees.
And he's got about 70.
"I observe at home above all the loyalty and pride of having engaged in something that has been generally recognized."
"This is not, and by far, the only result of my personal work, but the result of a good work of all of us together.
"Only my name is pushed forward," said Lucas Pytloun with modesty.
I wish my successor a better year than we had in Farmet.
The euphoria of victory was quickly replaced by the effects of the crisis.
Thanks to the sense of the goal of winner Farmet has the worst moments behind him.
The one who came to Slovansky dum for the first place of the competition for the Firm of the year organized by Vodaphone last year is Karel Zdarsky the owner of the company Farmet.
The jury rewarded the efforts with which it transformed a tool shop in Ceska Skalice into a firm with a turnover of SEK 100 million.
"I can say that the award not only encouraged me, my staff and increased our self-confidence to fight competition," said the winner of last year's competition today.
At the beginning of Farmet's history there was a desire to do something useful.
And so when the state proposed to Karel Zdrasky's father to rent the small workshop as compensation after the confiscation of property by the communists, he did not hesitate long, refused a career in a firm where he worked at the time, and created a company with some comrades in his father's entourage for the manufacture of plastic baths.
Not very long after they began to specialize in vegetable oil presses.
After eighteen years, it has become the largest manufacturer of automatic presses in Central Europe.
The company was known even to the non-specialized public after the success of the competition through the media.
"Not only did our customers really get to know the Farmet brand better, but also the foreign partners who started to realize that they were collaborating with a company that has achieved the greatest success in its country of origin," says Zdarsky.
But the past year has not been at Farmet only in the euphoria of victory.
The valuation of the company was based on the economic results of 2008 and in part of 2009.
And precisely in 2009 this was the most difficult year for the sale of engineering machines.
At the height of the crisis, which did not really affect citizens, companies were forced to stop their investment projects and begin to limit their purchases of new materials and technologies.
"We obviously did not escape this situation."
"The turnover dropped by 40 percent, and we had to limit our production and even lay off," Zdarsky explains.
A viable society must know that from time to time unpopular measures must be taken.
But they managed the situation properly and kept the results profitable even though they were inferior to those they had before the crisis.
However, in Farmet, they continued uncompromisingly to invest in research and development.
"We built with endowments a training and research center, strengthened the presentation of the company in international fairs and won the main awards in national exhibitions," says Zdarsky.
Everything leads us to believe that the crisis is behind them.
The numbers of affires go back and with them the number of employees also.
"To the new winner I wish this pleasant feeling of victory but in a calm atmosphere," said Karel Zdarsky.
The investigation that removes insane regulations.
The Absurdity of the Year investigation is for the fourth time part of the business clan.
Some absurd regulations could be removed.
The little glorious winner of this year's survey on the Absurdity of the Year was the obligation to bring to the offices documents that officials can obtain on-line.
More than one third of the 4,000 voters voted for this.
For example, the social affairs authorities requested a paper extract from the business register while the official could obtain it in two clicks of a mouse.
It changes because of the investigation.
"The Czech Social Insurance Administration will no longer require the extract from the Trade Register for insurance payment controls," said Jana Buranova, spokesperson for the Czech Social Insurance Administration (CSSZ).
To highlight all the regulations and decrees that companies and entrepreneurs have to fill in in the Czech Republic and to remove those that are absurd is the meaning of this contest of the Absurdity of the Year.
This survey is again this year for the fourth time part of the business clan organized by Hospodarske noviny and has even greater popularity.
