Compared to the world, the situation in the Czech Republic is not improving at all.
According to the World Bank, the Czech Republic is in 74th place in terms of business conditions, an increase of 8 places compared to last year.
The Absurdity of the Year competition was first launched in 2006 and continues each year under the same scenario.
Anyone can report administrative and bureaucratic absurdities every year from April to the end of September, the last time before the competition is closed.
