"I'm really fascinated by the fact that they want a seat at the Nuclear Security Summit 2012 Nuclear Security Summit."
"This proves to me that this process is working," said Ken Luongo, President of the Global Security Partnership, a group promoting nuclear security.
Clinton described the agreement as a "very significant, important step" made by Belarus.
Obama committed in Prague in April 2009 to secure all vulnerable nuclear material around the world in the next four years.
