It seems that President Zapatero also heard of this form and its double declaration (the reforms promised after the meeting of the past Saturday with the big companies and yesterday's announcement of the new measures) suggests that, despite Merkel's criticisms, we have opened the way to the thesis that it is necessary to put order at home.
But the red line Germany has drawn is there, and they don't seem to move it.
And among the possibilities we are considering, we cannot exclude the possibility of abandoning a monetary zone too full of countries that are not serious.
